  "doc_id": "13597",
  "text": "Insulin like growth factors (IGFs) are important mitogens acting as endocrine, paracrine and autocrine agents. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] They are present in most of the biological fluids and carried by specific binding proteins (IGFBPs). The major form of binding protein known in human circulation is IGFBP-3, which modulates IGF activity and also regulates cell growth and apoptosis.",
